SIMPLE: embattled
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Embattled
<hw>Em*bat"tled</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having
indentations like a battlement.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Having the edge broken like
battlements; -- said of a bearing such as a fess, bend, or the
like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Having been the place of battle; <as>as, an
<ex>embattled</ex> plain or field</as>.</def> <rj><au>J.
Baillie.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Embattlement</ent>⟦br⟧
